<h1 class=3D"center">Geometry</h1>=20


<p class=3D"center">Geometry is all about <b>shapes</b> and their propertie=
s.</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">If you like playing with objects, or like drawin=
g, then geometry is for you!</p>=20
<p>Geometry can be divided into:</p>=20
<p class=3D"floatLt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images=
/plane.svg" alt=3D"plane" height=3D"109" width=3D"250"></p>=20
<p><br>
<b><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/plane-geometry.html">Plan=
e Geometry</a></b> is about flat shapes like lines, circles and triangles .=
.. shapes that can be drawn on a piece of paper</p>=20
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>

<div class=3D"gap"></div>
<p class=3D"floatLt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images=
/3d-shapes.png" alt=3D"3d shapes" height=3D"110" width=3D"300"></p>=20
<p><br>
<b><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/solid-geometry.html">Soli=
d Geometry</a></b> is about three dimensional objects like cubes, prisms, c=
ylinders and spheres.</p>=20
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/style/right-arrow.gif"=
 alt=3D"right arrow" height=3D"46" width=3D"46"></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center;"><i>Hint: Try drawing some of the shapes=
 and angles as you learn ... it helps.</i></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20


<h2>Point, Line, Plane and Solid</h2>=20

<p class=3D"floatRt"><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/dimensi=
ons.html"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/dimensions=
.svg" alt=3D"dimensions" height=3D"148" width=3D"305"></a></p>=20
<p>A <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/point.html">Point</a> h=
as no <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/dimensions.html">dimen=
sions</a>, only position<br>
A <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/line.html">Line</a> is one=
-dimensional<br>
A <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/plane.html">Plane</a> is t=
wo dimensional (2D)<br>
A <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/solid-geometry.html">Solid=
</a> is three-dimensional (3D)</p>=20
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>


<h2>Why?</h2>=20

<p>Why do we do Geometry? To discover patterns, find areas, volumes, length=
s and angles, and better understand the world around us.</p>=20


